item.title: Investigating Relationship between Fatal Outcomes and Age Groups of COVID-19 Cases in Toronto
item.description: I. Introduction The COVID-19 pandemic is an ongoing pandemic of coronavirus disease 2019 (i.e.Â COVID-19) caused by severe acute respiratory syndrome coronavirus 2 (SARS-CoV-2).[1] The disease was first identified in December 2019 in Wuhan, China,[2] and soon subsequently recognized as a worldwide pandemic. As of 27 September 2020, around 17,000 cases have been reported in Toronto, Canada, resulting in more than 1,000 deaths; more than 15,000 people have recovered.[3]
